By Samuel Ajayi ABUJA (Sundiata Post) When Transparency International released corruption perception indices under Jonathan and previous regimes, they were doing a good job and a reliable organisation. In fact, the then ACN propaganda machinery, under this same Lai Mohammed, would always latch on it to pummel the then ruling party. This week, same TI released corruption perception and their assessment became “unfair and misleading”. In fact, Garba Shehu is asking TI to be more “transparent”. When you are looking a for a government that is every reflection of disaster, look no further than this Buhari regime. Bunch of clowns… Source: Facebook